vectorData.altText: 7. The ____________ nucleus of the trigeminal nerve and the __________ nucleus of the trigeminal nerve are located at the level of the mid pons. (2 answers separated by one space)
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.
That’s right!  Both chief sensory /main and motor nuclei of the trigeminal nerve are located at the level of the mid pons.

Which cranial nerve emerges from the lateral aspect of the mid-pons? Think, then click!     Trace the nerve into the brainstem to find its nuclei.
What is the function of this nerve?
Why are there two nuclei associated with this nerve?
sensory to the face, motor to the muscles of mastication
What two white matter bundles, associated with the cerebellum, are present at the mid-pons level?
The superior and middle cerebellar peduncles

Which cranial nerve emerges from the caudal pons, close to the midline? Trace the nerve into the brainstem to find its nucleus.
What is the function of this nerve?
It innervates the lateral rectus muscle. Lesion of CN VI or its nucleus causes difficulty abducting the eye. In addition, the eye rests in an adducted position. Can you explain this?

Which cranial nerve emerges from the caudal pons, more laterally? Trace the nerve into the brainstem to find its motor nucleus.
What is the function of this nerve?
Why is the facial colliculus called the facial colliculus?

Lesion of this nerve or its nucleus causes paralysis of the ipsilateral face, both the upper and lower regions.
It also carries some general sensory fibres, and so is associated with the spinal trigeminal nucleus. Identify the spinal trigeminal nucleus and its tract in the figure.
Motor to the muscles of facial expression
No, the abducens nucleus is deep to the facial colliculus. However, the fibres of the facial nerve arch around the abducens nucleus before they exit the brainstem.
Not because the facial nucleus is deep to it!
Where is the spinal trigeminal nucleus, which receives pain and temperature sensation from the face? Remember? It’s in the medulla. We’ll see it next.

One nucleus is the chief sensory nucleus of V, which receives fine touch from the face.
The other is the motor nucleus of V, which contains LMNs.

Which cranial nerve emerges from the caudal pons most laterally? Trace the nerve into the brainstem to find its nucleus.
What is the function of this nerve?
It carries sound information from the cochlea and balance information from the vestibular apparatus.
